</c01><c01 id="aspace_8459caeec7c8fc6dab46147f0214138c" level="file"><did><unittitle>Reprint from <title>Ithaca Journal</title> (undated) re: Horton's running for re-election as Justice, Supreme Court, 6th Judicial District (Democrat)</unittitle><abstract id="aspace_568d0e85dba74d8d9b262a119f34107a">Onetime Mayor of Ithaca 1909-1912(?); born Truxton 1850, lived in Cortland, Ithaca, attended Cornell; City Attorney; practiced law 1877-; circa. 1877-1928</abstract><container id="aspace_aed4944ab966d650904f9d64f21b2710" label="Mixed Materials [31924079228700]" type="box">2</container></did></c01><c01 id="aspace_85fcbcd79c64ea7a9a2e02366bef0e80" level="file"><did><unittitle>Typed carbon copy of a 9 pp. Report to Randolph Horton, Ithaca Mayor, Apr. 15, 1909</unittitle><abstract id="aspace_4a99d9e2d2dbdfc25adda3230eb5dd21">From the Mayor's Committee of Citizens (Jacob Rothschild, Walter McCormick, Robert C. Osborn, Charles C. Howell, Joseph Campbell) who considered and investigated the question of erecting a Hospital for contagious diseases in the City of Ithaca and providing for its operation and maintenance. The Report also includes a summary of early hospital facilities, 1889- .</abstract><container id="aspace_65706f360d51c82116c4db2473a65611" label="Mixed Materials [31924079228700]" type="box">2</container></did></c01><c01 id="aspace_1464b7ad4f883da5ca8fb6026dccd010" level="series"><did><unittitle>Ithaca Calendar Clock Co. - bankrupt 1917</unittitle></did><c02 id="aspace_d88f4f44a8a251eea42ff0224646e4f2" level="file"><did><unittitle>Co. Letterhead (samples)</unittitle></did></c02><c02 id="aspace_4c8b70695aa32bd502672c1d01c20580" level="file"><did><unittitle>Letters to Randolph Horton - Trustee for bondholders of I.C.C. - co. business (closing out - selling stock) - H.J. Bool Co., Inc. Ithaca,</unittitle><unitdate calendar="gregorian" era="ce" normal="1818/1819" type="inclusive">1818-1819</unitdate></did></c02><c02 id="aspace_dc6fd3cf324dbd48e7517a177e95fd20" level="fil